"""
NeuralFoil Aerodynamic Simulation Module — v4
==============================================
Evaluates all bird-inspired airfoils across a comprehensive flight-condition
matrix, extracts category-level performance champions, and exports a
dedicated champions CSV for downstream use.

Changes from v3
---------------
A.  BUG FIX — stall detection
    v3's docstring claimed the earliest-trigger among three methods won,
    but the implementation used a fixed priority order (peak_drop first).
    v4 genuinely compares all three triggers and picks the earliest α.
    The priority is now only a tiebreaker when methods agree exactly.

B.  BUG FIX — stall clipping removed
    v3 forced every stall angle into [8°, 18°] with np.clip, which
    silenced real variation across species. v4 removes the hard clip;
    implausible values are flagged instead (see `stall_plausible` column)
    and only bounded if they fall outside a much wider [4°, 22°] window.

C.  BUG FIX — slope threshold aligned with docstring
    v3 had 40% in the docstring and 15% in code. v4 uses 40% (the
    physically motivated value from Schlichting-type boundary-layer
    arguments) consistently.

D.  BUG FIX — LD_report used consistently
    v3 mixed LD_ratio (can contain NaN after filtering) and LD_report
    in summary statistics, biasing averages. v4 uses LD_report for all
    reported summary metrics and keeps LD_ratio only for debugging.

E.  BUG FIX — plausibility fallback is recorded
    When no plausible points exist and the code falls back to all data,
    v4 records `used_implausible_fallback=True` on the summary row so
    downstream consumers can filter these out.

F.  NEW — champions CSV (primary user request)
    The best bird in each category AND the overall top-N birds across
    all categories are exported to:
        champions_by_category.csv     (one row per category)
        overall_top_birds.csv         (top-N across all, sortable)
    Both contain the full summary columns so they're self-contained.

G.  CLEANUP
    - Removed unused imports (os, glob, warnings)
    - Fixed "2° steps" → "1° steps" in the report
    - Fixed the broken drag-correction-impact plot (now per-point scatter)
    - Added the correlation CSV path to the final printout

References
----------
Drela, M. (1989). XFOIL: An analysis and design system for low Reynolds
    number airfoils. *Low Reynolds Number Aerodynamics*, Springer.
Pennycuick, C. J. (2008). *Modelling the Flying Bird*. Elsevier.
Hedenström, A. & Alerstam, T. (1995). Optimal flight speed of birds.
    *Phil. Trans. R. Soc. B*, 348(1326), 471–487.
NeuralFoil documentation: github.com/peterdsharpe/NeuralFoil
"""

